message.content: cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MED, cs.NEURON - The paper proposes a deep learning-based approach for coronary calcium detection using CT scans, which falls under the domain of medical imaging. The use of attention mechanisms and gradient-weighted class activation mapping also suggests a focus on computer vision and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), followed by cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.MED (Medical Imaging), and cs.NEURON (Neurons and Cognition).
